Stats

The things that predicts the percentage of FSM students in a school are the percentage of FSM students in a LA and the progress 8 score of school. The higher the progress 8 (P8MEA), the lower the percentage of FSM students in a school (mean=3.66%; median=2.95%; sd=2.71% ):

Sch FSM % ~ Gender + LA FSM % + Region FSM % + Progress 8

We can also look at the shortfall in FSM places in a school through Sch-LA FSM short %, that is the percentage difference between the schools‚Äô FSM % and the FSM % for the Local Authority. The higher the number the bigger the difference between the number of FSM students in a school and that expected if it was representative of the local authority. Again, we see progress 8 significantly predicting the shortfall. The higher the progress 8, the less representative a school in terms of FSM students:

Sch-LA FSM short % ~ Gender + LA FSM % + Region FSM % + Progress 8
